Since Confluence 5.3, the file {{ehcache.xml}} no longer exists in the Confluence home directory. It has been replaced by the file ehcache.properties which has a different format. and now is no longer possible to edit the {{sizeOfPolicy}} property.

Please provide an easy way to edit that property.

+*Workaround:*+
# Make a copy of the file {{<CONFLUENCE_INSTALL>/confluence/WEB-INF/lib/confluence-cache-ehcache-5.4.4.jar}} and move it to a temporary folder.
# Unzip the copy of the file {{confluence-cache-ehcache-5.4.4.jar}}.
# From the uncompressed files, edit the file named {{ehcache.xml}} and enter the desired value in the {{sizeOfPolicy}} property.
# Compress the files back into {{confluence-cache-ehcache-5.4.4.jar}}
# Stop Confluence.
# Replace the file {{<CONFLUENCE_INSTALL>/confluence/WEB-INF/lib/confluence-cache-ehcache-5.4.4.jar}} with the modified version.
# Delete the content of these folders (if they exist):
#* {{<confluence-home>/bundled-plugins}}
#* {{<confluence-home>/plugin-cache}}
#* {{<confluence-home>/plugins-osgi-cache}}
#* {{<confluence-home>/plugins-temp}}
#* {{<confluence-home>/bundled-plugins_language}}
# Restart Confluence.

Please note that any changes you do to the file will be overridden next time you upgrade Confluence.

